🧪 4. DEBUG_NOTES.md (this saves HOURS later)

Document bugs like this one.

Writing
Debug Notes
Bug: Thu/Fri Task Misalignment
Symptoms
Appears mid-week (Wednesday)
Tasks shift incorrectly (Thu/Fri)
Self-corrects next day
Root Cause
getTaskState() used:
diff = targetDay - currentUTCDay
if(diff < 0) diff += 7
This forced incorrect week selection
Lesson
Week selection must consider cycle, not just day diff
⚙️ 5. CODE DISCIPLINE (VERY IMPORTANT)

You only need 3 rules:

Rule 1 — Single Source of Truth
ONLY getTaskState() is allowed to build Dates

No other function should do:

new Date(...) + task logic
Rule 2 — No Hidden Time Logic

If any function does:

setUTCHours / setUTCDate

👉 It must be documented.

Rule 3 — Separate Concerns
State → getTaskState
Display → render
Formatting → format functions

Never mix.

🧪 6. BUILT-IN TEST MODE (you already started this)

Keep this permanently:

function getNow(){
  return window.TEST_NOW ? new Date(window.TEST_NOW) : new Date();
}
How you use it:
window.TEST_NOW = "2026-04-08T14:00:00Z";
renderDouble();
renderTriple();

👉 This alone prevents 90% of future bugs.

🔁 7. STANDARD DEBUG FLOW (follow this every time)

When something breaks:

1. Check getTaskState() output
2. Log:
   - targetDay
   - currentUTCDay
   - base
3. Compare expected vs actual
4. THEN look at render

NOT the other way around.

